The paper deals with constructing sparse and light spanners for general graphs, which is a problem in graph algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient algorithm, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.SI (Systems and Control).
